The paper deals with the entropy of a random variable and its typical sets, which are concepts commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of log-concave distributions is also a common topic in computer science, particularly in optimization and machine learning, which fall under cs.DS and cs.LG, respectively. The paper's focus on smooth interpolation and continuity suggests a possible connection to signal processing and interpolation (cs.SI).
